The Prince was so far from being disgraced, that the King during his absence made him Commander in Chief of all his Forces in Zeland. For the Winter coming on, and the Dutch Fleet sailing towards Lubec to
Victual, and soon after putting into Port, and the Enemy at Land breaking up their Campagne, gave the King leisure to pass over into Sconen and so to Gottenburg, where he held a Convention of the States of his Kingdome, for the better facilitating of such new Levies of men, and other Contributions which were thought necessary for carrying on his many Wars to some desirable conclusion. And as his leisure permitted he intended to make an Excursion to Stockholm, that City much desiring to see their King after four years absence. But his incessant Labours, Dec. 1659. Care and Watchings brought him to a sharp defluxion;
that, a Feaver; and that, his end.
